Reexamination results showing tumor regression by contrast-enhanced CT scan. 
   (A) Occupation in mediastinum; 
   (B) thickening of the right pleura; 
   (C) soft tissue by the side of the right bronchial stump; 
   (D) metastatic lesion on the right upper abdomen. (A1, B1, C1, D1) PD after one cycle of first-line chemotherapy; (A2, B2, C2, D2) disease PR after two cycles of the second-line treatment; (A3, B3, C3, D3) disease remaining as PR after four cycles of the second-line treatment.
